<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,438,441,468]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brethes" authorityYear="1915" box="[286,438,441,468]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Austrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[286,438,441,468]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Austrothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="588" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,513,1043]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">
The generic name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brethes" authorityYear="1915" box="[363,502,513,539]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Austrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[363,502,513,539]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Austrothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a particular problem because the identity of the 
<typeStatus box="[1082,1130,513,539]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">type</typeStatus>
species remains unknown. Three further species have been described in this genus, and re-examination of the original specimens of each one has indicated that they are not closely related to each other, and that each requires a new generic placement. The genus was erected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Brethes" box="[397,564,620,647]" firstAuthor="Brethes" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" pagination="89 - 92" refId="ref3295" refString="Brethes, J. (1915) Descripcion de un Genero nuevo y una nueva especie de Thysanoptero de la Republica Argentina. Annales Museo Nacional, 27, 89 - 92." type="journal article" year="1915">Brethes (1915)</bibRefCitation>
for a single new species from 
<collectingCountry box="[906,1020,621,647]" name="Argentina" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Brethes. The" authorityName="Brethes. The" authorityYear="1915" box="[1031,1275,621,647]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Austrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verae">
<emphasis box="[1031,1048,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1063,1125,622,647]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">verae</emphasis>
Brethes. The
</taxonomicName>
only recorded population of this species was collected from a Basidiomycete fungus, and the description states and illustrates that the male is wingless with no ocelli and with a prominent narrow fore tarsal tooth. But 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brethes. The" authorityYear="1915" box="[1135,1197,694,719]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Austrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verae">
<emphasis box="[1135,1197,694,719]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">verae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been studied by any taxonomist other than the describer, and the original specimens appear to have been lost (teste Carlos de Borbon, 
<date box="[250,339,765,792]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" value="2019-11">xi.2019</date>
). The description, and the association with a Basidiomycete fungus, suggest that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brethes. The" authorityYear="1915" box="[1250,1312,766,791]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Austrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verae">
<emphasis box="[1250,1312,766,791]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">verae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs in some genus of fungus-feeding Phlaeothripinae. Indeed, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brethes" authorityYear="1915" box="[778,917,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Austrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[778,917,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Austrothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may prove to be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" box="[1274,1409,801,827]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Hoplothrips" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1274,1409,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Hoplothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a worldwide genus exhibiting much variation in structure among species (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound" box="[952,1164,837,863]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Mound" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" pagination="301 - 323" refId="ref3546" refString="Mound, L. A., Wang, J. &amp; Tree, D. J. (2020) The genus Hoplothrips in Australia (Thysanoptera, Phlaeothripinae), with eleven new species. Zootaxa, 4718 (3), 301 - 323. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4718.3.1" type="journal article" year="2020">
Mound 
<emphasis box="[1041,1089,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">et al</emphasis>
. 2020
</bibRefCitation>
). The name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brethes" authorityYear="1915" box="[1297,1436,837,863]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Austrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1297,1436,837,863]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Austrothrips</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
thus becomes a 
<emphasis box="[330,495,873,899]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">nomen dubium</emphasis>
, as well as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brethes. The" authorityYear="1915" box="[626,688,874,899]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" genus="Austrothrips" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="verae">
<emphasis box="[626,688,874,899]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">verae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, until such time that suitable specimens can be collected in 
<collectingCountry name="Argentina" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Argentina</collectingCountry>
. The three other species described in the genus seem to have been placed there primarily because of the presence of long, capitate major setae on the pronotum, and the descriptions do not provide suitable character states for reassessing their relationships within the Phlaeothripinae. Original material of each of these species has therefore been studied, and each species is here transferred to a different genus.
</paragraph>
